captions.text:
And today, we're going to be
doing a new and improved room

We're finally going to show
you guys our new room in Texas.

-And we just decided
to change the look.

We wanted more of
like a mature--
So my mom helped us design it.
And I can't wait to show you.

-So first, we'll show
you our bathroom.

We're super excited,
again, to have

a bathroom connected
to our bedroom.

And we had to share with
all the other girls.

So it's nice to have
our own bathroom.

And we actually have
all our jewelry.

-And then, we just made hooks
to hook onto our jewelry.

-And yeah, then it just holds
our earrings and our bracelets.

It's really helpful
and super cute.

And we'll move on
to the bedroom.

So next, we will show
you guys our beds.

But first, we'll start
with our old antique chest.

-I think, because they were
going around antiquing.

-Yeah, but basically, just
holds all of our blankets.

And then behind it, we have
a secret bookshelf down here.
It protects all of our books.

It's where we keep all
of our favorite books,

you know, make our room
look more organized

and saves space, so, oh, it's
a bookshelf and so we're good.

-It makes our room look
clean, and it's just perfect.

-So next, we'll
show you our beds.

These are our beds, and the
bedding and all the pillows

And we made this arrangement,
because in our old room,

we had two beds that were--
you know, they were sideways,
They took up the entire bedroom.

-We felt like we didn't
have enough space.

I don't know what you would
call it, but it works.

It's just these two flat beds,
and we put mattresses on it
and put them into an L-shape.
And so Brooklyn lays this way.

-So this is our
arrangement for beds.

And as I said
before, the bedding,

the pillows, everything
is from Pottery Barn.

-And it's just a gray
cream, white, gold mixture.

-And down here, we just
have these little black--

they're like bucket sort
of material, buckets.

And they hold a bunch
of stuff, just whatever
you want to put down there.

Something like that,
where they have

the cubby holes underneath,
and then the mattress on top.

-So that's the kind
of bed that we have.

So it makes the room
look clean and organized.

And you just have these
cute little cubbies

and boxes to hold
all of your stuff.

So we'll move on to
our board of pictures.

-Well, this kind of like
our magnetic bulletin board.

We just hang up pictures of
all of our friends and family

And over here is my
little Trim-a-Rim circle.

And it's a white board-- I
like to write quotes on it--

and it has a little rim
where you can create whatever

you want, put whatever you want
on it, like pictures, slides.

So I just put that up there
because I thought it went well.

And these little
lights around it

just are left over lights
from our seventh grade vice

And so we just hung
them up because we've

got to give it more
of a teenager twist.

This is what we like
to call our Pixar lamp.

And for those of you who
don't know what that is,
it's a lamp that goes like this.
So this is our Pixar lamp.

You all want a Pixar
lamp, I know you do!

-We're going to turn towards
this little guy over here.

-This is my favorite part
about our bedroom, honestly.

We've seen this in
magazines and stuff.
But we liked the deer better.

-And it just matches
the whole theme.

-I think it just
spices everything up,

-And then, we have
our black B, which

I think we had in
our old bedroom.

-Because we made it
a couple years ago.
We need double B's for that.

We should make a
pink one for me.

and it's Macintosh,
like the apple

or like the computer brand,
whatever you like to prefer.

And that will just keep
things centered, mm!

-Just don't forget to
blow out your candle.

-So safety with candles
in your bedroom.

Next, our night stand, we've
had this one for a couple years.

-I don't really know
what it's called.

-I think they got it
from Missouri again.

Missouri has the
best antique stores.

-So if you're in
Missouri, go antinquing.

And then, we have
our iHome down here.

I don't know if you can see
it, but iHomes are iHomes.

Nothing more you
can say about it.
And he got it from Pottery Barn.
And I love it so much.

It just kind of brings
in the grayness--

And the carpet, if you can
see it, it's from Target.

And again, it's just added
into the creams and the grays--

-And then, we have these
amazing frames on our walls.

The frames are just,
again, from antique stores.

And then, the wordings, like
the words painted on them,

-And they have
stick-on things, so you
can stick them on the wall.

So basically, we just hung
up some frames and words

It's like half the size
of our Utah closet.

But then again, we
got lucky because it's

a nice walk-in closet,
and we have enough room
to store all of our clothes.

-We have a bajillion
little cubbies in there

This is our grand mirror, and
we got it from Hobby Lobby.
And I must say, it weighs--

-My Dad can attest to that
because he hung it up.

-So thank you, Dad,
for hanging that up.

But it's awesome because
it's full length.

-And you'll love
having it in here.

-Look at your outfits
in the morning.
And you can pose in front.

-Thank you guys so,
so much for watching
our new and improved room tour.

-Be sure to leave a
comment below on what

your favorite part
of our room was.

And we'll see you
guys next week.

-And then she
joined in, and there

was like a duet in
history class today!
